Subject: [PATCH 4/4] Add freeze discipline: signatures ratified only by
 compiling prototypes

- New normative rule in the architecture spec: no public signature is frozen
  merely for looking elegant in the document; every canonical signature must
  be demonstrated by at least one compilable Odin example and one behavior
  test before freezing. Specification text proposes; compiling prototypes
  ratify
- Phase 1 Spec Gate restructured around this discipline, with an explicit
  frozen/not-frozen split: the gate freezes the minimal public API, Context
  and lifetimes, extractors, responses, conceptual transport contract,
  dispatch, test transport, and minimal conformance suite; it deliberately
  leaves out post-next onion semantics, threading guarantees, final arena
  design, optimized radix tree, OpenAPI, streaming, WebSocket, and the
  definitive Transport shape, each decided at its own later gate on
  implementation evidence
- Agent prompt updated with the corresponding process rules

